createNote(string,string,string).details: The details of the note are stored as part of the Notes struct in the contract's state. A unique id for each note is also generated based on the user address, current timestamp, title and keywords.

params.description: - This is the content of the note that will be added to the blockchain.
params.keywords: - These are additional details about the note used for search functionality in the future if required.
params.title: - This is the title of the note which will be added to the blockchain.

returns._0: Returns a Note struct which contains information about each note including id, nextNote pointer, user address, title, description, timestamp and updated.

createNote(string,string,string).notice: This function allows a user to create a new note with given title, description and keywords.
